  "summary": "Malicious code in next-locomotive-init (npm)",
  "details": "The package next-locomotive-init@1.0.0 is a combosquat package impersonating Next.js animation utilities. On install, the postinstall.js hook collects the system username and hostname via os.userInfo().username and os.hostname(), formats them as an email address, and POSTs the data to eng0ai-sdk[.]vercel[.]app/api/telemetry. The package contains no animation functionality — its sole purpose is this host-metadata beacon.",
